&gt;  code above?
&gt;  Also, if I have a method with @Before annotation, then it won&#39;t run
&gt;  when I run the test.

The behavior you&#39;re seeing is because you&#39;re running the test with a
JUnit 3.8 test runner. Try converting your test to follow the JUnit 4
API by getting rid of the &quot;junit.framework&quot; imports:

import static org.junit.Assert.assertNull;
import org.junit.Test;

public class MultiAttacherTest {
    @Test
    public final void strongComponentWalk() {
        assertNull(null);
    }
}


